This paper involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques to analyze online discourse, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of transformers for text similarity also suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves social media analysis, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of machine learning models for classification could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or software engineering (cs.SE).
